'''{{PAGENAME}}''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūkuōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=99 ōji Shrines}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]]. <!--PAGENAME magic word should be substituted in the future when this is moved to its final pagename. This was added to a few pages not created on Feb 8 because they were very barren and this gives context to the fact that they are in a large group of pages all to be translated more or less as a group similar to the Ise Shrines--> ==Overview== {{Shrine | Name = {{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子}} | Image = [[File:篠田王子跡.jpeg|thumb|200px|篠田王子跡]] | Location = {{ill|Ōji-chō|ja|王子町}}, {{ill|Izumi, Osaka|ja|和泉市}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府}}, Japan | Coordinates = | Deity = | Affiliation = {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道}} - {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野信仰}} | Established = | Map = }}
'''{{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子}}''' (しのだおうじ) was the 9th {{ill|Kumano Ōji|ja|九十九王子}} shrine along the historic {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道}} pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists.
== History == While the shrine itself has not survived, a stone monument marks the former site of Shinoda Ōji. This monument is located in a residential area slightly south of the {{ill|Hijiri Shrine (Izumi)|ja|聖神社}} torii gate, which stands along the Kumano Kōdō in {{ill|Ōji-chō|ja|王子町}} 3-chōme, {{ill|Izumi, Osaka|ja|和泉市}}.
== Access == * The nearest station to the stone monument is **{{ill|Kita-Shinoda Station|ja|北信太駅}}** on the {{ill|Hanwa Line|ja|阪和線}}, operated by {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道}}.
