'''Shinoda Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūkuōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|12=draft|12=draft}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== {{Shrine | Name = {{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子|12=draft|12=draft}} | image = [[File:篠田王子跡.jpeg|thumb|200px|篠田王子跡]] | location = {{ill|Ōji-chō|ja|王子町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Izumi, Osaka|ja|和泉市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|12=draft|12=draft}}, Japan | coordinates = | deity = | Affiliation = {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft|12=draft}} - {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野信仰|1=Kumano Three Shrines|lt=Kumano faith|12=draft|12=draft}} | Established = | Map = }}
'''{{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (しのだおうじ) was the 9th {{ill|Kumano Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft|12=draft}} shrine along the historic {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft|12=draft}} pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists.
== History == While the shrine itself has not survived, a stone monument marks the former site of Shinoda Ōji. This monument is located in a residential area slightly south of the {{ill|Hijiri Shrine (Izumi)|ja|聖神社|12=draft|12=draft}} torii gate, which stands along the Kumano Kōdō in {{ill|Ōji-chō|ja|王子町|12=draft|12=draft}} 3-chōme, {{ill|Izumi, Osaka|ja|和泉市|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Access == * The nearest station to the stone monument is '''{{ill|Kita-Shinoda Station|ja|北信太駅|12=draft|12=draft}}''' on the {{ill|Hanwa Line|ja|阪和線|12=draft|12=draft}}, operated by {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== See also == * {{ill|Kumano Sanzan|ja|熊野三山|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft|12=draft}} - {{ill|Kiiji|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft|12=draft}} *: {{ill|Ōtorii Ōji|ja|大鳥居王子|12=draft|12=draft}} * '''{{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子|12=draft|12=draft}}''' - {{ill|Hiramatsu Ōji|ja|平松王子|12=draft|12=draft}}
