'''Shinoda Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūkuōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== {{Shrine | Name = {{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | image = [[File:篠田王子跡.jpeg|thumb|200px|篠田王子跡]] | location = {{ill|Ōji-chō|ja|王子町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Izumi, Osaka|ja|和泉市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan | coordinates = | deity = | Affiliation = {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野信仰|1=Kumano Three Shrines|lt=Kumano faith|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Established = | Map = }}
'''{{ill|Shinoda Ōji|ja|篠田王子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' (しのだおうじ) was the 9th {{ill|Kumano Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft}} shrine along the historic {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists.
== History == While the shrine itself has not survived, a stone monument marks the former site of Shinoda Ōji. This monument is located in a residential area slightly south of the {{ill|Hijiri Shrine (Izumi)|ja|聖神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} torii gate, which stands along the Kumano Kōdō in {{ill|Ōji-chō|ja|王子町|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3-chōme, {{ill|Izumi, Osaka|ja|和泉市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Access == * The nearest station to the stone monument is '''{{ill|Kita-Shinoda Station|ja|北信太駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' on the {{ill|Hanwa Line|ja|阪和線|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, operated by {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
